workflow.name: Auto-translate YouTube videos to Japanese with DeepL and post to Slack
workflow.description:
## Overview
Auto-translate YouTube uploads to Japanese and post to Slack (DeepL + Slack)

## Who‚Äôs it for
Marketing or community teams that follow English-speaking creators but share updates with Japanese audiences; language learners who want JP summaries of newly released videos; internal comms teams curating industry channels for a JP workspace.

## What it does
This workflow detects new YouTube uploads, retrieves full metadata, translates the title and description into Japanese using DeepL, and posts a formatted message to a Slack channel. It also skips non-English titles to avoid unnecessary translation.
## How it works
„ÉªRSS watches a channel for new items.
„ÉªYouTube API fetches the full snippet (title/description).
„ÉªText is combined into a single payload and sent to DeepL.
„ÉªThe translated result + original metadata is merged and posted to Slack.

## Requirements
„ÉªYouTube OAuth (for reliable snippet retrieval)
„ÉªDeepL API key (Free or Pro)
„ÉªSlack OAuth

## How to set up
„ÉªDuplicate this template.
„ÉªOpen the Config (Set) node and fill in YT_CHANNEL_ID, TARGET_LANG, SLACK_CHANNEL.
„ÉªConnect credentials for YouTube, DeepL, and Slack (don‚Äôt hardcode API keys in HTTP nodes).
„ÉªClick Execute workflow and verify one sample post.

## How to customize
„ÉªChange TARGET_LANG to any language supported by DeepL.
„ÉªAdd filters (exclude Shorts, skip videos under N characters).
„ÉªSwitch to Slack Blocks for richer formatting or thread replies.
„ÉªAdd a fallback translator or retry logic on HTTP errors.
## Notes & limits
DeepL Free/Pro have different endpoints/quotas and monthly character limits. YouTube and Slack also enforce rate limits. Keep credentials in n8n‚Äôs credential store; do not commit keys into templates. Rotate keys if you accidentally exposed them.

„ÉªYouTube API fetches the full snippet (title/description).
„ÉªText is combined into a single payload and sent to DeepL.
„ÉªThe translated result + original metadata is merged and posted to Slack.

## Requirements
„ÉªYouTube OAuth (for reliable snippet retrieval)
„ÉªDeepL API key (Free or Pro)
„ÉªSlack OAuth

## How to set up
„ÉªDuplicate this template.
„ÉªOpen the Config (Set) node and fill in YT_CHANNEL_ID, TARGET_LANG, SLACK_CHANNEL.
„ÉªConnect credentials for YouTube, DeepL, and Slack (don‚Äôt hardcode API keys in HTTP nodes).
„ÉªClick Execute workflow and verify one sample post.

## How to customize
„ÉªChange TARGET_LANG to any language supported by DeepL.
„ÉªAdd filters (exclude Shorts, skip videos under N characters).
„ÉªSwitch to Slack Blocks for richer formatting or thread replies.
„ÉªAdd a fallback translator or retry logic on HTTP errors.
## Notes & limits
DeepL Free/Pro have different endpoints/quotas and monthly character limits. YouTube and Slack also enforce rate limits. Keep credentials in n8n‚Äôs credential store; do not commit keys into templates. Rotate keys if you accidentally exposed them.

## Send a Message (Skipped)

1Ô∏è‚É£ Connect YouTube, DeepL, and Slack credentials
2Ô∏è‚É£ Update the RSS channel ID
3Ô∏è‚É£ Adjust Slack channel name if needed
4Ô∏è‚É£ Test with one video manually

(Optional) Embed a quick Loom video for reviewers.

## Format YouTube Data for DeepL

üß† Prepare Translation Input
Combines YouTube data into a single formatted text:
„ÄêTitle„Äë
{title}

„ÄêDescription„Äë
{description}

## Language Filter
üîé Filter English Titles Only
Skips non-English titles based on regex (^[A-Za-z0-9\\s\\W]+$).
If true ‚Üí proceed to translation.
If false ‚Üí send ‚Äúskipped‚Äù message to Slack.

## RSS Trigger

‚è∞ Trigger for new uploads
Checks the target YouTube channel RSS feed for new video posts.
Automatically passes new entries to the next node.

## Merge

üîó Combine Original + Translated Data
Joins DeepL translation results with YouTube metadata.
Output: unified object ready for Slack posting.

## Translate with DeepL

üåç Translate text into Japanese
Uses the DeepL API (POST request).
Translates the combined YouTube text.
Returns JSON with translated output.
‚ö†Ô∏è Never hardcode API keys ‚Äî store in credentials.

## Get a Video
üé¨ Retrieve Full Video Details
Uses the YouTube API to fetch snippet information such as title and description.
Input: video ID from RSS.
Output: structured JSON for downstream processing.

## Setup checklist
1) Connect: YouTube OAuth / DeepL / Slack
2) Open ‚ÄúSet (Config)‚Äù and fill: YT_CHANNEL_ID, TARGET_LANG, SLACK_CHANNEL
3) Replace DeepL HTTP node with DeepL credential (no hardcoded key)
4) Run once with a recent video to validate
5) Optional: turn on Error Trigger ‚Üí Slack #alerts

## Send to Slack
üí¨ Post Translated Message to Slack
Sends formatted message to a selected channel.
Includes both translated and original texts with a video link.
Example output:

##  Format Translated Output

This Code node formats the DeepL translation result into a clean JSON object 
that can be sent to Slack or other integrations.
Input:
- Translated text (from DeepL)
- Original title and description
Output:
{
  "translated_title": "...",
  "translated_description": "...",
  "original_title": "...",
  "url": "..."
}

Tip:
If you modify the Slack message format, adjust field names here.

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
